{"title_page": "Integrated Pollution Prevention and Control", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox EU legislation \n|type=Directive\n|title= IPPC Directive\n|number=   2008/1/EC\n|madeby=[[European Parliament]] & [[European Council|Council]]\n|madeunder= Article 175(1)\n|OJref= OJL 24 of 29 January 2008, pp. 8\u201329\n|OJrefurl= http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:L:2008:024:0008:0029:EN:PDF\n|made= 15 January 2008\n|commenced=18 February 2008\n|implementation= \n|CommProp= \n|ESCOpin= \n|ParlOpin= \n|Reports= \n|replaces= Directive 96/61/EC\n|amends= \n|amendedby= \n|replacedby=\n|status=Current\n}}\nDirective 2008/1/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 15 January 2008 concerning '''integrated pollution prevention and control''' is a [[Directive (European Union)|directive]] of the [[European Union]]. It replaces the [[European Council|Council]] Directive 96/61/EC of 24 September 1996 on the same subject matter; both are commonly referred to as '''IPPC Directive'''.\n\nFrom 2005 to 2007, the effect of the directive was assessed. In 2010, a revised wording was published, integrated with 6 other European directives regulating large industrial sites, into the [[Industrial Emissions Directive]], short '''IED'''.<ref>[http://ec.europa.eu/prelex/detail_dossier_real.cfm?CL=en&DosId=196594 European Commission PreLex Monitoring]</ref>\n\n== European IPPC Bureau ==\nThe European IPPC Bureau has been founded to organise the necessary exchange of information and produces [[Best Available Technology|Best Available Techniques]] (short: 'BAT') and reference documents (short: 'BREF') which Member States are required to take into account when determining best available techniques generally or in specific cases.\n\n=== Similar agencies===\n*[[Climate Change Agreement]]\n*[[United States Environmental Protection Agency|US EPA]] \u2013 SPCC\n\n==See also==\n*[[Best Available Techniques Reference Document (BREF)]]\n*[[NanoMemPro IPPC Database]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n== External links==\n*[http://europa.eu/legislation_summaries/environment/waste_management/l28045_en.htm EU legislation summary]\n*[http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:L:2008:024:0008:0029:EN:PDF Text of the directive (pdf)]\n*[http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=CELEX:32008L0001:EN:NOT Text of directive with headers (html)]\n*[http://eippcb.jrc.ec.europa.eu/  European    IPPC Bureau home page]\n*[http://www.curia.europa.eu/common/biblio/bib200506parteA.pdf The implementation of the IPPC Directive in Latvia / Edward Lestrade. A.540.991.28. European current law. October (2005), p. xi\u2013xv. 984.988]\n*[http://www.csb.gov.tr/projeler/ippc/ Ministry of Environment and Urbanism of Turkey, EU Project to implement Chapters 1 and 2 of the Industrial Emissions Directive (repealing IPPC Directive), explanations in Turkish and English]\n\n[[Category:European Union directives]]\n[[Category:2008 in the environment]]\n[[Category:Environmental law in the European Union]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox EU legislation \n|type=Directive\n|title= IPPC Directive\n|number=   2008/1/EC\n|madeby=[[European Parliament]] & [[European Council|Council]]\n|madeunder= Article 175(1)\n|OJref= OJL 24 of 29 January 2008, pp. 8\u201329\n|OJrefurl= http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:L:2008:024:0008:0029:EN:PDF\n|made= 15 January 2008\n|commenced=18 February 2008\n|implementation= \n|CommProp= \n|ESCOpin= \n|ParlOpin= \n|Reports= \n|replaces= Directive 96/61/EC\n|amends= \n|amendedby= \n|replacedby=\n|status=Current\n}}\nDirective 2008/1/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 15 January 2008 concerning '''integrated pollution prevention and control''' is a [[Directive (European Union)|directive]] of the [[European Union]]. It replaces the [[European Council|Council]] Directive 96/61/EC of 24 September 1996 on the same subject matter; both are commonly referred to as '''IPPC Directive'''.\n\nFrom 2005 to 2007, the effect of the directive was assessed. In 2010, a revised wording was published, integrated with 6 other European directives regulating large industrial sites, into the [[Industrial Emissions Directive]], short '''IED'''.<ref>[http://ec.europa.eu/prelex/detail_dossier_real.cfm?CL=en&DosId=196594 European Commission PreLex Monitoring]</ref>\n\n== European IPPC Bureau ==\nThe European IPPC Bureau has been founded to organise the necessary exchange of information and produces [[Best Available Technology|Best Available Techniques]] (short: 'BAT') and reference documents (short: 'BREF') which Member States are required to take into account when determining best available techniques generally or in specific cases.\n\n=== Similar Agencies===\n*[[Climate Change Agreement]]\n*[[United States Environmental Protection Agency|US EPA]] \u2013 SPCC\n\n==See also==\n*[[NanoMemPro IPPC Database]]\n*[[Best Available Techniques Reference Document (BREF)]]\n\n== External links==\n*[http://europa.eu/legislation_summaries/environment/waste_management/l28045_en.htm EU legislation summary]\n*[http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:L:2008:024:0008:0029:EN:PDF Text of the directive (pdf)]\n*[http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=CELEX:32008L0001:EN:NOT Text of directive with headers (html)]\n*[http://eippcb.jrc.ec.europa.eu/  European    IPPC Bureau home page]\n*[http://www.curia.europa.eu/common/biblio/bib200506parteA.pdf The implementation of the IPPC Directive in Latvia / Edward Lestrade. A.540.991.28. European current law. October (2005), p. xi\u2013xv. 984.988]\n*[http://www.csb.gov.tr/projeler/ippc/ Ministry of Environment and Urbanism of Turkey, EU Project to implement Chapters 1 and 2 of the Industrial Emissions Directive (repealing IPPC Directive), explanations in Turkish and English]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:European Union directives]]\n[[Category:2008 in the environment]]\n[[Category:Environmental law in the European Union]]\n", "name_user": "Me, Myself, and I are Here", "label": "safe", "comment": "alpha, cap, layout", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integrated_Pollution_Prevention_and_Control"}
{"title_page": "Audie Award", "text_new": "{{Refimprove|date=May 2019}}\nAn '''Audie Award''' (or '''Audie''') is an annual award given by the American [[Audio Publishers Association]] for [[audiobook]]s and [[spoken-word]] entertainment.  Since 1996, the nominees have been announced in February, and the winners announced at a gala banquet held in May, usually during the [[BookExpo America]] fair. The Audies are sometimes promoted as \"the [[Academy Awards|Oscars]] of the audiobook industry\" and serve as a way to promote audiobooks.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.audiofilemagazine.com/features/A2079_Audies08.pdf |title=The Audies Finalists 2008 |work=[[AudioFile (magazine)|AudioFile]] |author= |date=2008 |accessdate=January 10, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424127887323854904578637850049098298 |title=The New Explosion in Audio Books |work=[[Wall Street Journal]] |author=Alexandra Alter |date=August 1, 2013 |accessdate=June 2, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAwards are given in about thirty categories. Some of the awards relate to types of writing, including abridged and unabridged fiction and non-fiction, and such [[genre]]s as [[romance novels|romance]], [[Fantasy literature|fantasy]] and [[mystery novels|mystery]]; other awards recognize excellence in different styles of narration and production, such as multi-voiced performance and production values. Over the years, the structure and the categories of the awards have changed. These changes are apparent in the lists of the Audie award winners in the external links below.\n\nThe 2016 award ceremony was held May 11 at the [[Adler Planetarium]] in [[Chicago]] and was hosted by [[Paula Poundstone]].<ref>[http://www.audiopub.org/Audies2016/Audies_Nominations_Release.pdf Audie Nominations 2016 Press Release] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160221215153/http://www.audiopub.org/Audies2016/Audies_Nominations_Release.pdf |date=February 21, 2016 }} February 2016</ref>\n\n==Award categories==\nThe award categories, effective 2019, are:\n\n=== Overall ===\n*Audiobook of the Year \n*Original Work \n*[[Radio drama|Audio Drama]]\n\n=== Narration talent ===\n*Best Female Narrator \n*Best Male Narrator \n*Multi-Voiced Performance ''(multiple readers with little to no interaction)''\n*Narration by the Author or Authors\n\n=== Genre ===\n*''[[Fiction]]:''\n**[[Fiction]] ''(titles that do not fit into a specific fiction category listed below)'' \n**[[Literary Fiction]] & Classics \n**[[Mystery fiction|Mystery]]\n**[[Thriller (genre)|Thriller / Suspense]]\n**[[Science Fiction]]\n**[[Fantasy]] \n**[[Romance novel|Romance]]\n*''[[Non-Fiction]]:''\n**[[Non-Fiction]] ''(titles that do not fit into a specific non-fiction category listed below)''\n**[[History]] / [[Biography]]\n**[[Autobiography]] / [[Memoir]] \n**[[Business development|Business]] / [[Personal Development]]\n\n*[[Inspirational fiction|Faith-Based Fiction]] or Non-Fiction \n*[[Humor]] \n*[[Short story|Short Stories]] / Collections\n\n*''Youth:''\n**Young Listeners ''(Up to Age 8)'' \n**Middle Grade ''(Ages 8-11)'' \n**Young Adult ''(Ages 12-18)''\n\n=== Infrequent award categories ===\n*Excellence in Design [formerly Package Design]\n*Excellence in Marketing\n*Excellence in Production \n*Hall of Fame\n*Judge's Award\n*Spanish Language\n*Special Achievement\n\n=== Defunct or superseded award categories ''(as of 2019)'' ===\n*Achievement in Abridgement (defunct)\n*Audio, Licensed or Distributed (defunct)\n*Audio Adaptation (defunct) \n*Biography / Memoir (superseded)\n*Business / Educational (superseded)\n*Business Information (superseded)\n*Classics (superseded)\n*Education and Training (superseded)\n*[[Erotica]] (defunct)\n*Fiction, Abridged (defunct)\n*History (superseded)\n*Inspiration & Faith-Based Fiction (superseded)\n*Inspiration & Faith-Based Non-Fiction (superseded)\n*Literary Fiction (superseded)\n*Multi-Voiced Narration (defunct)\n*New Publisher (defunct)\n*Non-Fiction, Abridged (defunct)\n*[[Paranormal]] (defunct)\n*Personal Development (superseded)\n*Poetry (defunct)\n\n== Award winners==\nHere is a table of award winners.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.audiopub.org/winners|title=Audie Award\u00ae Winners - APA|website=Audiopub.org|accessdate=11 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Overall categories ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|'''Audiobook \n'''of the Year'''\n \n''(first presented 2004)''\n|{{bulleted list\n|2019<ref name=\"Nineteen\">{{cite news |last1=Katz |first1=Danielle |title=Audies Press Release Winners Final (2019) |url=https://www.audiofilemagazine.com/content/uploaded/media/audies-press-release-winners-final.pdf |accessdate=17 May 2019 |agency=AudioFileMagazine.com |publisher=Audio Publishers Agency (APA) |date=5 March 2019}}</ref>: '''''[[Children of Blood and Bone]]'''''<ref>{{cite web |title=Reviews: Children of Blood and Bone |url=https://www.audiofilemagazine.com/reviews/read/138353/ |website=AudioFileMagazine.com |publisher=AudioFile Publications, Inc. |accessdate=17 May 2019}}</ref> by [[Tomi Adeyemi]]. Narrated by [[Bahni Turpin]]. \n|2018<ref name=\"Eighteen\">{{cite web |title=Audies Award Finalists and Winners 2018 |url=https://www.audiofilemagazine.com/audies/2018/?category=&winners=true |website=AudioFileMagazine.com |publisher=AudioFile Publications, Inc. |accessdate=17 May 2019}}</ref>: '''''[[Lincoln in the Bardo]]''''' by [[George Saunders]]. Narrated by the author, [[Nick Offerman]], [[David Sedaris]], and a full cast.\n|2017<ref name=\"Seventeen\">{{cite web |title=Audies Award Finalists and Winners 2017 |url=https://www.audiofilemagazine.com/audies/2017/ |website=AudioFileMagazine.com |publisher=AudioFile Publications, Inc. |accessdate=17 May 2019}}</ref>: '''''Hamilton: The Revolution''''' by [[Lin-Manuel Miranda]] and Jeremy McCarter. Narrated by [[Mariska Hargitay]], with the authors.\n|2016<ref name=\"Sixteen\">{{cite web |title=Audie Award Finalists and Winners 2016 |url=https://www.audiofilemagazine.com/audies/2016/ |website=AudioFileMagazine.com |publisher=AudioFile Publications, Inc. |accessdate=17 May 2019}}</ref>: '''''[[The Girl on the Train (novel)|The Girl on the Train]]: A Novel''''' by [[Paula Hawkins (author)|Paula Hawkins]], Narrated by [[Clare Corbett]], [[Louise Brealey]], and [[India Fisher]]. \n|2015<ref name=\"Fifteen\">{{cite web |title=Audie Award Finalists and Winners 2015 |url=https://www.audiofilemagazine.com/audies/2015/ |website=AudioFileMagazine.com |publisher=AudioFile Publications, Inc. |accessdate=17 May 2019}}</ref>: '''''Mandela: An Audio History''''' by [[Nelson Mandela]]. Narrated by the author, [[Desmond Tutu]], and Joe Richman.\n|2014<ref name=\"Fourteen\">{{cite web |title=Audies Award Finalists and Winners 2014 |url=https://www.audiofilemagazine.com/audies/2014/ |website=AudioFileMagazine.com |publisher=AudioFile Publications, Inc. |accessdate=17 May 2019}}</ref>: '''''Still Foolin' 'Em: Where I've Been, Where I'm Going, and Where The Hell are My Keys'''''written and narrated by [[Billy Crystal]].\n|2013<ref name=\"BLR2013\">{{cite news |last1=Burkey |first1=Mary |title=#Audies 2013 |url=https://www.booklistreader.com/2013/05/30/book-news/audies-2013/ |accessdate=20 May 2019 |work=BookListReader.com |publisher=BookList Publications, a division of the ALA |date=May 30, 2013}}</ref>: '''''[[The End of the Affair]]''''' by [[Graham Green]]. Narrated by [[Colin Firth]].\n|2012<ref name=\"BLR2012\">{{cite news |last1=Burkey |first1=Mary |title=#JIAM2012 Audies Awards announced |url=https://www.booklistreader.com/2012/06/06/book-news/jiam2012-audies-awards-announced/ |accessdate=20 May 2019 |work=BookListReader.com |publisher=BookList Publications, a division of the ALA |date=June 6, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Twelve\">{{cite news |title=Audie Award Winners: Best Audio Books 2012 [Library Staff-created list] |url=https://seattle.bibliocommons.com/list/share/86922331/113123884 |accessdate=20 May 2019 |agency=Seattle Quick Picks by The Seattle Public Library |publisher=Seattle.Bibliocommons.com}}</ref>: '''''[[Bossypants]]''''', written and narrated by [[Tina Fey]]y.\n|2011<ref name=\"BookListReader2011\">{{cite news |last1=Burkey |first1=Mary |title=2011 Audies Award Winners |url=https://www.booklistreader.com/2011/05/25/audiobooks/2011-audies-award-winners/ |accessdate=20 May 2019 |work=BookListReader.com |publisher=BookList Publications, a division of the ALA |date=May 25, 2011}}</ref>: '''''Life''''' by [[Keith Richards]]. Narrated by the author, [[Johnny Depp]], and [[Joe Hurley]].\n|2010<ref name=\"BLR2010\">{{cite news |last1=Burkey |first1=Mary |title=Audies Awards 2010 |url=https://www.booklistreader.com/2010/05/25/audiobooks/audies-awards-2010/ |accessdate=22 May 2019 |work=BookListReader.com |publisher=BookList Publications, a division of the ALA |date=May 25, 2010}}</ref>: '''''Nelson Mandela's Favorite African Folktales''''' by [[Nelson Mandela]]. Narrated by full cast.\n|2009<ref name=\"BLR2009\">{{cite news |last1=Burkey |first1=Mary |title=2009 Audies Awards |url=https://www.booklistreader.com/2009/05/29/audiobooks/2009-audies-awards/ |accessdate=21 May 2019 |work=BookListReader.com |publisher=BookList Publications, a division of the ALA |date=May 29, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=The Graveyard Book |url=https://www.downpour.com/the-graveyard-book?sp=39043 |website=Downpour.com |publisher=Downpour.com, a division of Blackstone Publishing |accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref>: '''''The Graveyard Book''''' written and narrated by [[Neil Gaiman]]. \n|2008<ref name=\"LOL2008\">{{cite news |title=Audie Award Winners of 2008 (partial) |url=https://www.learnoutloud.com/Content/Topic-Pages/Audie-Award-Winners-of-2008/141 |accessdate=22 May 2019 |work=LearnOutLoud.com |issue=E-Magazine No. 070 |publisher=LearnOutLoud, Inc. |date=June 5, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Graff |first1=Keir |title=Chopin Wins the Audie |url=https://www.booklistreader.com/2008/06/02/book-awards/chopin-wins-the-audie/ |access