lzi]]. Narrated by [[Zachary Quinto]]. \n|2016<ref name=\"Sixteen\"></ref>: ''The Starling Project: An Audible Drama'' by [[Jeffery Deaver]]. Narrated by Alfred Molina and a full cast. \n|2015<ref name=\"Fifteen\"></ref>: ''Mandela: An Audio History'' by [[Nelson Mandela]]. Narrated by [[Desmond Tutu]], [[Nelson Mandela]], and Joe Richman.\n|2014<ref name=\"Fourteen\"></ref>: ''Thirteen'' by [[Scott Harrison (writer)|Scott Harrison]], George Mann, Mark Morris, [[Kaaron Warren]], Martin Day, Gary McMahon, Cavan Scott, Dan Abnett, Alasdair Stuart, Kim Newman, Mark Wright, Simon Clark, and Johnny Mains, Narrated by Barnaby Edwards, et al. \n|2013<ref name=\"BLR2013\"></ref>: ''Gun Church'' by [[Reed Farrel Coleman]]. Narrated by Joe Barrett and John Keating. \n|2012<ref name=\"BLR2012\"></ref>: ''Metatropolis: Cascadia'' by [[Jay Lake]], [[Mary Robinette Kowal]], [[Elizabeth Bear]], [[Ken Scholes]], Karl Schroeder, and Tobias Buckell. Narrated by [[Ren\u00e9 Auberjonois]], [[Kate Mulgrew]], [[Wil Wheaton]], [[Gates McFadden]], [[Jonathan Frakes]], and [[LeVar Burton]].\n|2011<ref name=\"BookListReader2011\"></ref>: ''New Adventures of Mickey Spillane\u2019s Mike Hammer Vol 2'' by Max Allan Collins. Narrated by [[Stacy Keach]] and a full cast. \n|2010<ref name=\"BLR2010\"></ref>: ''Tell Me a Story 3: Women of Wonder'' by Amy Friedman. Narrated by Bryce Dallas Howard, Paula Poundstone, Wendy Hammers, [[Margot Rose]], [[Jessica DiCicco]], and Yvette Freeman. \n|2009<ref name=\"BLR2009\"></ref>: ''Louis Vuitton Soundwalk, China: Beijing'' by Stephan Crasneanscki. Narrated by Gong Li.\n|2008<ref name=\"VOX2008\" />: ''[[Sweeney Todd]] and [[The String of Pearls]]'' by [[Yuri Rasovsky]]. Narrated by Phil Proctor, Simon Templeman, Moira Quirk, Martin Jarvis, Rosalind Ayres, Robertson Dean, and W. Morgan Sheppard. \n|2007<ref name=\"IPOL2007\"></ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Pearl Gluck |url=http://cityvisions.ccny.cuny.edu/2012/Ipearl.html |website=CityVisions.ccny.cuny.edu |pub