l Shorto]]. Narrated by L.J. Ganser. \n|2004<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[Charlie Wilson's War: The Extraordinary Story of the Largest Covert Operation in History]]'' by [[George Crile III|George Crile]]. Narrated by Christopher Lane. \n|2003<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''3000 Degrees: The True Story of a Deadly Fire and the Men Who Fought It'' by Sean Flynn. Narrated by Richard Rohan.\n|2002<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[John Adams (book)|John Adams]]'' by [[David McCullough]]. Narrated by Nelson Runger.\n|2001<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[The Measure of a Man: A Spiritual Autobiography|The Measure of a Man]]'' written and narrated by [[Sidney Poitier]]. }}\n|-\n|'''History'''\n\n'''/ Biography'''\n|{{bulleted list\n|2019<ref name=\"Nineteen\"></ref>: ''Darkest Hour'' by [[Anthony McCarten]]. Narrated by John Lee.\n|2018<ref name=\"Eighteen\"></ref>: ''Loving Vs. Virginia'' by Patricia Hruby Powell. Narrated by Adenrele Ojo and MacLeod Andrews. \n|2017<ref name=\"Seventeen\"></ref>: ''In Harm\u2019s Way: The Sinking of the USS Indianapolis and the Extraordinary Story of its Survivors '' by [[Doug Stanton]]. Narrated by Mark Boyett. \n|2016<ref name=\"Sixteen\"></ref>: ''[[A Man on the Moon]]: The Voyages of the Apollo Astronauts'' by [[Andrew Chaikin]] and [[Tom Hanks]]. Narrated by [[Bronson Pinchot]]. \n|2015<ref name=\"Fifteen\"></ref>: ''The Bully Pulpit: [[Theodore Roosevelt]], [[William Howard Taft]], and the Golden Age of Journalism '' by [[Doris Kearns Goodwin]]. Narrated by [[Edward Herrmann#Voice Work|Edward Herrmann]]. }}\n'''''2014: See separate defunct categories \"History\" and \"Biography/Memoir\" for winners prior to 2015''''' \n|-\n|'''Autobiography'''\n\n'''/ Memoir'''\n|{{bulleted list\n|2019<ref name=\"Nineteen\"></ref>: ''[[Educated (book)|Educated]]'' by [[Tara Westover]]. Narrated by '''[[Julia Whelan]]'''.\n|2018<ref name=\"Eighteen\"></ref>: ''[[Born to Run]]'' written and narrated by [[Bruce Springsteen]]. \n|2017<ref n