92 }}</ref>: ''[[Spoiled Rotten America]]: Outrages of Everyday Life'' written and narrated by [[Larry Miller (comedian)|Larry Miller]]. \n|2006<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[The Truth (With Jokes)]]'' written and narrated by [[Al Franken]].\n|2005<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[Dress Your Family in Corduroy and Denim]]'' written and narrated by [[David Sedaris]].\n|2004<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''David Sedaris: Live at Carnegie Hall'' written and narrated by [[David Sedaris]].\n|2003<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''Things You Shouldn't Say Past Midnight'' by Peter Ackerman. Narrated by Jeffrey Donovan, [[Richard Kind]], Clea Lewis, Alan Mandell, Mandy Siegfried, and Joey Slotnick.\n|2002<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[Napalm & Silly Putty]]'' written and narrated by [[George Carlin]]. \n|2001<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[Bridget Jones: The Edge of Reason]]'' by [[Helen Fielding]]. Narrated by Tracie Bennett. }}\n|-\n|'''Short Stories'''\n\n'''/ Collection'''\n|{{bulleted list\n|2019<ref name=\"Nineteen\"></ref>: ''Heads of the Colored People'' by Nafissa Thompson-Spires. Narrated by Adenrele Ojo.\n|2018<ref name=\"Eighteen\"></ref>: ''The Language of Thorns: Midnight Tales and Dangerous Magic'' by Leigh Bardugo. Narrated by Lauren Fortgang. \n|2017<ref name=\"Seventeen\"></ref>: ''The Brink: Stories'' by Austin Bunn. Narrated by Austin Bunn, Luke Daniels, Tanya Eby, Ralph Lister, Amy McFadden, Mikael Naramore, and Nick Podehl. }} \n'''''2016<ref name=\"Sixteen\"></ref>: *Award not listed on website*'''''\n{{bulleted list\n|2015<ref name=\"Fifteen\"></ref>: ''The Assassination of Margaret Thatcher: Stories'' by Hilary Mantel. Narrated by Jane Carr. \n|2014<ref name=\"Fourteen\"></ref>: ''Sherlock Holmes in America'' by Jon L. Lellenberg, Martin H. Greenberg, and Daniel Stashower. Narrated by Graeme Malcolm. \n|2013<ref name=\"BLR2013\"></ref>: ''Astry'' by Emma Donoghue. Narrated by Khristine Hvam, James Langton, Robert Petkoff, Suzanne Toren, and Dion Graham. \n|2012<ref name=\"BLR2012\"></ref>: ''Selected Shorts: New American Stories'' by Aleksandar Hemon, Jhumpa Lahirir, Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie, and Sherman Alexie. Narrated by Boyd Gaines, Rita Wolf, Condola Rashad, and BD Wong. \n|2011<ref name=\"BookListReader2011\"></ref>: ''Stories: All-New Tales'' by Neil Gaiman. Narrated by Anne Bobby, Jonathan Davis, Peter Francis James, Katherine Kellgren, and Euan Morton. \n|2010<ref name=\"BLR2010\"></ref>: ''The Black Mask Audio Magazine, Vol. 1: Classic Hard-Boiled Tales From the Original Black Mask'' by Hugh B. Cave, Paul Cain, Frederick Nebel, Reuben J. Shay, Dashiell Hammett, and William Cole. Narrated by a full cast.\n|2009<ref name=\"BLR2009\"></ref>: ''[[Armageddon in Retrospect]]: And Other New and Unpublished Writings on War and Peace'' by [[Kurt Vonnegut]]. Narrated by Rip Torn and Michael Vonnegut.\n|2008<ref>{{cite web |title=Audible '20th Century Ghosts' [listing] |url=https://www.audible.com/pd/20th-Century-Ghosts-Audiobook/B0036KRFBI?ref=a_ep_audie-_c8_lProduct_15_9&pf_rd_p=bab774e3-a06e-4f9d-ba8e-5f2838406ba4&pf_rd_r=Z95GN0SJT6FM69X763SS |website=Audible.com |publisher=Audible, Inc. |accessdate=22 May 2019}}</ref>: ''[[20th Century Ghosts]]'' by [[Joe Hill (writer)|Joe Hill]]. Narrated by David Ledoux. \n|2007<ref name=\"IPOL2007\"></ref>: ''[[This I Believe]]: The Personal Philosophies of Remarkable Men and Women'' by [[Jay Allison]] and [[Dan Gediman]]. Narrated by Bill Gates, Martha Graham, et al.\n|2006<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[Runaway (book)|Runaway: Stories]]'' by [[Alice Munro]]. Narrated by Kymberly Dakin.\n|2005<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[Dress Your Family in Corduroy and Denim]]'' written and narrated by [[David Sedaris]].\n|2004<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''Home on the Prairie: Stories from [[Lake Wobegon]]'' written and narrated by [[Garrison Keillor]].\n|2003<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''Classic Women's Short Stories'' by Katherine Mansfield, Kate C