 Gillette, and Yuri Rasovsky. Narrated by Martin Jarvis, Kristoffer Tabori, and a full cast. \n|2005<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''Buddha Boy'' by Kathe Koja. Narrated by Spencer Murphy and the Full Cast Family.\n|2004<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''The Complete [[Arkangel Shakespeare]]'' by [[William Shakespeare]]. Narrated by a full cast. \n|2003<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[The Guys]]'' by [[Anne Nelson]]. Narrated by [[Swoosie Kurtz]] and Bill Irwin.}}\n'''''Prior to 2003, this award category was titled: \"Theatrical Performance\"'''''\n{{bulleted list\n|2002: '''''no winner listed on audiopub.org'''''.\n|2001<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[Agnes of God]]'' by [[John Pielmeier]]. Narrated by Barbara Bain, Emily Bergl, and Harriet Harris. }}\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Narration talent categories ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|'''Best Female \n'''Narrator'''\n|{{bulleted list\n|2019<ref name=\"Nineteen\"></ref>: '''[[Julia Whelan]]''', Narrator. ''[[Educated (book)|Educated]]'' by [[Tara Westover]].\n|2018<ref name=\"Eighteen\"></ref>: '''[[Bahni Turpin]]<ref name=\"BahniNHF\">{{cite web |title=The Narrator Hall of Fame: Bahni Turpin |url=https://www.audible.com/ep/NHOF_BahniTurpin |website=Audible.com |publisher=Audible, Inc. |accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref>''', Narrator. ''[[The Hate U Give]]<ref name=\"BahniNHF\"></ref>'' by [[Angie Thomas]]. \n|2017<ref name=\"Seventeen\"></ref>: '''Tavia Gilbert'''<ref>{{cite web |title=Tavia Gilbert: Performer, Writer, Producer |url=http://taviagilbert.com/ |website=TaviaGilbert.com |accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref>, Narrator. ''Be Frank with Me'' by Julie Claiborne Johnson. \n|2016<ref name=\"Sixteen\"></ref>: '''[[Katherine Kellgren]]<ref name=\"KKObit\">{{cite news |title=Katherine Kjellgren Obituary |url=https://www.legacy.com/obituaries/nytimes/obituary.aspx?n=katherine-kjellgren&pid=187871203 |accessdate=21 May 2019 |work=Legacy.com |publisher=The New York Times Company |date=January 17, 2018}}</ref>''', Narrator. ''Wild Rover No More: Being the Last Recorded Account of the Life & Times of Jacky Faber'' by [[L.A. Meyer]]. }}\n'''''Prior to 2016, this award category was titled: \"Solo Narration-Female\"'''''\n{{bulleted list\n|2015<ref name=\"Fifteen\"></ref>: '''[[Bahni Turpin]]''', Narrator. ''Yellow Crocus'' by Laila Ibrahim. \n|2014<ref name=\"Fourteen\"></ref>: '''[[Katherine Kellgren]]<ref name=\"KKObit\"></ref>''', Narrator. ''The Twelve Clues of Christmas: A Royal Spyness Mystery'' by [[Rhys Bowen]]. \n|2013<ref name=\"BLR2013\"></ref>: '''[[Katherine Kellgren]]<ref name=\"KKObit\"></ref>''', Narrator. ''The Boys in the Suitcase: A Nina Borgh Mystery'' by [[Lene Kaaberb\u00f8l]] and [[Agnete Friis (writer)|Agnete Friis]]. \n|2012<ref name=\"BLR2012\"></ref>: '''[[Rosalyn Landor]]'''<ref>{{cite news |title=Spotlight on Popular Narrators: Rosalyn Landor |url=https://www.audiofilemagazine.com/narrators/rosalyn-landor/ |accessdate=21 May 2019 |work=AudioFileMagazine.com |publisher=AudioFile Publications, Inc.}}</ref>, Narrator. ''The Winter Sea'' by [[Susanna Kearsley]]. \n|2011<ref name=\"BookListReader2011\"></ref>: '''[[Alfre Woodard]]''', Narrator. ''Glorius'' by [[Bernice McFadden]]. \n|2010<ref name=\"BLR2010\"></ref>: '''[[Jenna Lamia]]''', Narrator. ''The Chosen One: A Novel'' by [[Carol Lynch Williams|Carol Williams]].\n|2009<ref name=\"BLR2009\"></ref>: '''[[Katherine Kellgren]]<ref name=\"KKObit\"></ref>''', Narrator. ''[[Curse of the Blue Tattoo]]: Being an Account of the Misadventures of Jacky Faber, Midshipman and Fine Lady'' by [[L.A. Meyer]].\n|2008<ref name=\"Audible2008B\">{{cite web |title=Audie Awards (2008 partial B)|url=https://www.audible.com/ep/audie_award?pf_rd_m=A2ZO8JX97D5MN9&pf_rd_r=9ZFSM2WDCKKHDSYDCWKZ&pf_rd_s=center-4&ref_=amb_link_VHb9PR0lN9-ZMoC2KpGY4w_28&rw_useCurrentProtocol=1&page=15 |website=Audible.com |publisher=Audible, Inc. |accessdate=22 May 2019}}</ref>: '''Lorelei King'''<ref name=\"LK2008\">{{cite web |title=Lorelei King Audiobooks: Tallgrass |url=https://www.loreleiking.com/tallgrass.html |website=LoreleiKing.com |accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref>, Narrator. ''Tallgrass''<ref name=\"LK2008\"></ref> by [[Sandra Dallas]].\n|2007<ref name=\"IPOL2007\"></ref>: '''[[Annie Potts]]''', Narrator. ''Telegraph Days'' by [[Larry McMurtry]].\n|2006<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''Davina Porter''', Narrator. ''A Breath of Snow and Ashes: Outlander, Book 6'' by Diana Gabaldon.\n|2005<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''Lisette Lecat''', Narrator. ''The Full Cupboard of Life: More from the No. 1 Ladies' Detective Agency'' by Alexander McCall Smith. \n|2004<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''[[Barbara Rosenblat]]''', Narrator. ''[[The Nazi Officer's Wife]]: How One Jewish Woman Survived the Holocaust'' by Edith Hahn Beer.\n|2003<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''[[Barbara Rosenblat]]''', Narrator. ''Bronx Primitive: Portraits in a Childhood'' by [[Kate Simon]].\n|2002<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''Dearbhla Molloy''', Narrator. ''My Dream of You'' by [[Nuala O'Faolain]]. \n|2001<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''[[Ruby Dee]]''', Narrator.  ''[[Their Eyes Were Watching God]]'' by [[Zora Neale Hurston]]. }}\n|-\n|'''Best Male \n'''Narrator'''\n|{{bulleted list\n|2019<ref name=\"Nineteen\"></ref>: '''[[Edoardo Ballerini]]'''<ref>{{cite news |last1=Charles |first1=Ron |title=Book World: Eve Ensler waited decades for an apology from her abusive father. She finally wrote one herself |url=https://www.sfgate.com/entertainment/article/Book-World-Eve-Ensler-waited-decades-for-an-13841058.php |accessdate=17 May 2019 |agency=SFGate |work=The Washington Post |date=13 May 2019}}</ref>, Narrator. ''[[Watchers (novel)|Watchers]]'' by [[Dean Koontz]].\n|2018<ref name=\"Eighteen\"></ref>: '''[[Trevor Noah]]''', Narrator & Author. ''[[Born a Crime]]: Stories from a South African Childhood'' by [[Trevor Noah]] \n|2017<ref name=\"Seventeen\"></ref>: '''Simon Vance''', Narrator.  ''[[Jerusalem (Moore novel)|Jerusalem]]'' by [[Alan Moore]]. \n|2016<ref name=\"Sixteen\"></ref>: '''[[George Guidall]]''', Narrator. ''[[The English Spy]], Gabriel Allon, Book 15'' by [[Daniel Silva (novelist)|Daniel Silva]]. }}\n'''''Prior to 2016, this award category was titled: \"Solo Narration-Male\"'''''\n{{bulleted list\n|2015<ref name=\"Fifteen\"></ref>: '''[[Bronson Pinchot]]''', Narrator. ''The Hero's Guide to Being an Outlaw'' by Christopher Healy. \n|2014<ref name=\"Fourteen\"></ref>: '''[[David Pittu]]''', Narrator. ''[[The Goldfinch (novel)|The Goldfinch]]'' by [[Donna Tartt]]. \n|2013<ref name=\"BLR2013\"></ref>: '''[[Edoardo Ballerini]]''', Narrator.  ''[[Beautiful Ruins]]'' by [[Jess Walter]]. \n|2012<ref name=\"BLR2012\"></ref><ref name=\"Twelve\"></ref>: '''Simon Vance''', Narrator.  ''[[The King's Speech]]: How One Man Saved the British Monarchy'' by Mark Logue and [[Peter Conradi]]. \n|2011<ref name=\"BookListReader2011\"></ref>: '''[[Alan Cumming]]''', Narrator. ''[[Zorgamazoo]]'' by [[Robert Paul Weston]]. \n|2010<ref name=\"BLR2010\"></ref>: '''Charlton Griffin''', Narrator.  ''[[Great Expectations]]'' by [[Charles Dickens]]. \n|2009<ref name=\"BLR2009\"></ref>: '''John Lee''', Narrator.  ''[[The Count of Monte Cristo]]'' by [[Alexandre Dumas]].\n|2008<ref name=\"VOX2008\" />: '''[[Jim Dale]]''', Narrator. ''[[Harry Potter and The Deathly Hallows]]'' by [[J.K. Rowling]].\n|2007<ref name=\"IPOL2007\"></ref>: '''[[Jim Dale]]''', Narrator. ''[[Peter and the Shadow Thieves]]: The Starcatchers, Book 2'' by [[Dave Barry]] and [[Ridley Pearson]]. \n|2006<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''William Hootkins''', Narrator. ''Moby Dick'' by Herman Melville. \n|2005<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''[[Jim Dale]]''', Narrator. ''Peter and the Starcatchers'' by Dave Barry and Ridley Pearson.\n|2004<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''[[Will Patton]]''', Narrator. ''Last Car to Elysian Fields: A [[Dave Robicheaux]] Novel'' by [[James Lee Burke]]. \n|2003<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: '''[[Frank Muller]]''', Narr