 Spencer]], and [[Bahni Turpin]]<ref name=\"BahniNHF\"></ref>. \n|2009<ref name=\"BLR2009\"></ref>: ''[[Duma Key]]'' by [[Stephen King]]. Narrated by [[John Slattery]]. \n|2008<ref name=\"Audible2008B\"></ref>: ''Tallgrass''<ref name=\"LK2008\"></ref> by [[Sandra Dallas]]. Narrated by Lorelei King<ref name=\"LK2008\"></ref>. }}\n'''''Prior to 2008, this award category was titled \"Fiction, Unabridged\"'''''\n{{bulleted list\n|2007<ref name=\"IPOL2007\"></ref>: ''Rise and Shine'' by [[Anna Quindlen]]. Narrated by Carol Monda. \n|2006<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''A Slight Trick of the Mind'' by Mitch Cullin. Narrated by Simon Jones.\n|2005<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''The Darling'' by Russell Banks. Narrated by Mary Beth Hurt.\n|2004<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[All Over Creation]]'' by [[Ruth Ozeki]]. Narrated by [[Kate Fleming|Anna Fields]].\n|2003<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[Middlesex (novel)|Middlesex]]'' by [[Jeffrey Eugenides]]. Narrated by [[Kristoffer Tabori]].\n|2002<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[The Talisman (King and Straub novel)|The Talisman]]'' by [[Stephen King]] and [[Peter Straub]]. Narrated by [[Frank Muller]]. \n|2001<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''[[Fierce Invalids Home from Hot Climates]]'' by [[Tom Robbins]]. Narrated by [[Keith Szarabajka]]. }}\n|-\n|'''Literary Fiction'''\n\n'''/ Classics'''\n|{{bulleted list\n|2019<ref name=\"Nineteen\"></ref>: ''[[Bleak House]]'' by [[Charles Dickens]]. Narrated by [[Miriam Margolyes]].\n|2018<ref name=\"Eighteen\"></ref>: ''House of Names'' by [[Colm T\u00f3ib\u00edn|Colm Toibin]]. Narrated by [[Juliet Stevenson]], et al. \n|2017<ref name=\"Seventeen\"></ref>: ''[[Homegoing (Gyasi novel)|Homegoing]]'' by [[Yaa Gyasi]]. Narrated by Dominic Hoffman. \n|2016<ref name=\"Sixteen\"></ref>: ''Little Big Man'' by [[Thomas Berger (novelist)|Thomas Berger]]. Narrated by Scott Sowers, cameo by David Aaron Baker. }}\n'''''2015: See separate defunct categories \"Literary Fiction\" and \"Classi