 Mullally]].\n|2018<ref name=\"Eighteen\"></ref>: ''Carpet Diem: Or...How to Save the World by Accident'' by Justin Lee Anderson. Narrated by [[Matthew Lloyd Davies]]. \n|2017<ref name=\"Seventeen\"></ref>: ''I\u2019m Judging You '' written and narrated by [[Luvvie Ajayi]]. \n|2016<ref name=\"Sixteen\"></ref>: ''Furiously Happy: A Funny Book About Horrible Things '' written and narrated by [[Jenny Lawson]]. \n|2015<ref name=\"Fifteen\"></ref>: ''Yes, Please '' by [[Amy Poehler]]. Narrated by [[Amy Poehler]], [[Carol Burnett]], [[Seth Meyers]], [[Michael Schur|Mike Schur]], Eileen and William Poehler, [[Patrick Stewart]], and [[Kathleen Turner]].\n|2014<ref name=\"Fourteen\"></ref>: ''Still Foolin' 'Em: Where I've Been, Where I'm Going, and Where The Hell are My Keys'' written and narrated by [[Billy Crystal]]. \n|2013<ref name=\"BLR2013\"></ref>: ''I Suck at Girls '' by [[Justin Halpern]]. Narrated by [[Sean Schemmel]]. \n|2012<ref name=\"BLR2012\"></ref><ref name=\"Twelve\"></ref>: ''Shatner Rules: Your Guide to Understanding the Shatnerverse and the World at Large '' by [[William Shatner]] with [[Chris Regan]]. Narrated by [[William Shatner]]. \n|2011<ref name=\"BookListReader2011\"></ref>: ''Old Jews Telling Jokes: 5000 Years of Funny Bits and Not-So-Kosher Laughs '' by [[Sam Hoffman]] with Eric Spiegelman. Narrated by [[Sam Hoffman]] with Eric Spiegelman and a full cast. \n|2010<ref name=\"BLR2010\"></ref>: ''Church People: the Lutherans of Lake Wobegon '' by [[Garrison Keillor]]. Narrated by [[Garrison Keillor]] and a full cast.\n|2009<ref name=\"BLR2009\"></ref>: ''The Learners'' by [[Chip Kidd]]. Narrated by [[Bronson Pinchot]].\n|2008<ref name=\"LOL2008\"></ref><ref name=\"Audible2008B\"></ref>: ''I Am America (And So Can You!)'' by Stephen Colbert. Narrated by Stephen Colbert with Paul Dinello, Kevin Dorff, Greg Hollimon, Evie McGee, David Pasquesi, Amy Sedaris, Allison Silverman, Brian Stack, and Jon Stewart.\n|2007<ref name=\"IPOL2007\"></ref><ref>{{cite 