1\"></ref>: ''The Intelligent Entrepreneur: How Three Harvard Business School Graduates Learned the 10 Rules of Successful Entrepreneurship'' by Bill Murphy, Jr. Narrated by LJ Ganser and Fred Berman. \n|2010<ref name=\"BLR2010\"></ref>: ''Rain: What a Paperboy Learned About Business'' written and narrated by Jeffrey J. Fox.\n|2009<ref name=\"BLR2009\"></ref>: ''The Little Red Book of Selling: 12.5 Principles of Sales Greatness'' written and narrated by [[Jeffrey Gitomer]]. }}\n'''''From 2002 through 2008, this award category was titled \"Business Information/Educational\"'''''\n{{bulleted list \n|2008<ref name=\"LOL2008\"></ref><ref name=\"Audible2008A\"></ref>: ''Words That Work: It's Not What You Say, It's What People Hear'' by Dr. Frank Luntz. Narrated by Dr. Frank Luntz and L.J. Ganser.\n|2007<ref name=\"IPOL2007\"></ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Greene |first1=Jo-Ann |title=Narrator's first book is a winner |url=https://lancasteronline.com/news/narrator-s-first-book-is-a-winner/article_1e23fe60-09ae-5012-99f2-518d311792fe.html |accessdate=22 May 2019 |work=LancasterOnline.com |publisher=LNP Media Group, Inc. |date=August 19, 2007}}</ref>: ''The Long Tail: Why the Future of Business Is Selling Less of More'' by Chris Anderson. Narrated by Christopher Nissley. \n|2006<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''Good to Great: Why Some Companies Make the Leap...And Others Don't'' written and narrated by Jim Collins.\n|2005<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''Death by Meeting: A Leadership Fable about Solving the Most Painful Problem in Business'' by Patrick Lencioni. Narrated by Jack Arthur.\n|2004<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''Use What You've Got, & Other Business Lessons I Learned from My Mom'' by [[Barbara Corcoran]] and [[Bruce Littlefield]]. Narrated by [[Barbara Corcoran]]. \n|2003<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''The Art of Profitability'' by [[Adrian Slywotzky]]. Narrated by Scott Mosenson and [[Jack Ong]].\n|2002<ref name=\"LCLAudies\"></ref>: ''Rich Kid Smart Kid: G